<h2>Solar Incentives in Tucson</h2>
<p>Tucson homeowners can take advantage of multiple solar incentives to reduce installation costs. The federal solar Investment Tax Credit (ITC) provides a 30% tax credit on the total system cost through 2032, then decreases to 26% in 2033 and 22% in 2034. Arizona offers additional state-level benefits, including a 25% state tax credit up to \$1,000 for solar installations, though this program has limited funding. TEP participates in Arizona's net metering program, allowing customers to receive credit for excess solar energy fed back into the grid at the full retail rate. Property tax exemptions are also available in Arizona, meaning the added home value from solar panels won't increase property taxes. Additionally, TEP occasionally offers rebates for solar installations, though these programs have limited availability and funding.</p>

<h2>Best Solar Companies in Tucson</h2>
<p>When selecting a solar installer in Tucson, prioritize companies with proper Arizona licensing, including a contractor's license and electrical license. Look for installers with extensive local experience who understand Tucson's specific permitting requirements and TEP's interconnection procedures. Top-rated companies should offer comprehensive warranties, typically including 20-25 year production warranties, 10-12 year equipment warranties, and 5-10 year workmanship warranties. Verify that installers are certified by the North American Board of Certified Energy Practitioners (NABCEP) and check their Better Business Bureau ratings and online reviews. Reputable Tucson solar companies will provide detailed proposals with system specifications, energy production estimates based on local weather data, and clear explanations of all available incentives. Always obtain multiple quotes and ensure the installer handles all permitting and utility interconnection paperwork with TEP.</p>

